    <!-- Graduate Students Section -->
    <section id="grad-section" class="space-y-3 rounded-lg px-5 py-6 md:px-6 md:py-7 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-accent">For Graduate Students</h2>
      <p class="text-muted max-w-3xl">
        The FROST Lab is an excellent environment for graduate research. We support both MS thesis projects and PhD dissertations across robotics, perception, autonomy, and systems engineering.
      </p>

      <Steps
        title="Joining the Lab as a Graduate Student"
        classes={{
          container: '!py-2 md:!py-3 !px-0',
          headline: {
            container: '!mb-3 text-left rtl:text-right',
            title: 'text-2xl md:text-3xl',
            subtitle: 'text-base text-muted',
          },
        }}
        items={[
          {
            title: 'Contact Faculty Directly',
            description:
              `Email professors whose research aligns with your interests. Share your CV, research statement, and specific projects or topics that excite you.`,
            icon: 'tabler:mail',
          },
          {
            title: 'Discuss Research Fit',
            description:
              `Have a conversation about potential thesis/dissertation topics, available funding, timeline, and lab culture. Ensure your goals and interests align with faculty expectations and ongoing research directions.`,
            icon: 'tabler:users',
          },
          {
            title: 'Apply to BYU Graduate Programs',
            description:
              `Once you've identified an advisor and discussed research, apply to the relevant BYU graduate program.`,
            icon: 'tabler:clipboard-check',
          },
        ]}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Non-BYU Undergraduate Students Section -->
    <section id="non-byu-section" class="space-y-4 rounded-lg px-5 py-6 md:px-6 md:py-7 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-accent">For Non-BYU Undergraduate Students</h2>
      <p class="text-muted max-w-3xl">
        Interested in spending a summer with the FROST Lab? The best pathway for non-BYU students is the Robotics Pioneers REU Summer Program hosted at BYU.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 border-l-4 border-emerald-500 p-6 rounded">
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Robotics Pioneers REU</h3>
        <p class="text-muted mb-3">A paid, 10-week immersive research experience for undergraduate students outside of BYU.</p>
        <a
          class="inline-flex items-center text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-200 font-semibold hover:underline"
          href="https://robotics.byu.edu/reu"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Apply at robotics.byu.edu/reu
          <span aria-hidden="true" class="ml-2">â†’</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-muted">If you have questions about fit or projects, reach out to a lab faculty memberâ€”let us know your interests and prior experience so we can advise on the application.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- General Information Section -->
    <section id="questions-section" class="space-y-3 rounded-lg px-5 py-6 md:px-6 md:py-7 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-accent">Questions? Let's Chat</h2>
      <p class="text-muted">
        The best way to learn about opportunities in the FROST Lab is to reach out directly. Visit our <a href="/people" class="text-accent hover:underline">People</a> page to find contact information for faculty and graduate students, or check out our <a href="/publications" class="text-accent hover:underline">Publications</a> to see the kinds of problems we solve.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted">Whether you're a freshman curious about robotics or a prospective graduate student with a specific research vision, don't hesitate to reach out!</p>
    </section>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
